<?xml version="1.0" encoding="utf-8" standalone="yes"?><rss version="2.0" xmlns:atom="http://www.w3.org/2005/Atom"><channel><title>Free on ErrorCode — Error Code Reference &amp; Solutions</title><link>https://errorcode.excellentwiki.com/tags/free/</link><description>Recent content in Free on ErrorCode — Error Code Reference &amp; Solutions</description><generator>Hugo</generator><language>en</language><atom:link href="https://errorcode.excellentwiki.com/tags/free/index.xml" rel="self" type="application/rss+xml"/><item><title>[Solution] C Double Free or Corruption — Freeing Already-Freed Memory Fix</title><link>https://errorcode.excellentwiki.com/languages/c/double-free/</link><pubDate>Mon, 01 Jan 0001 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate><guid>https://errorcode.excellentwiki.com/languages/c/double-free/</guid><description>&lt;h1 id="solution-c-double-free-or-corruption--freeing-already-freed-memory-fix"&gt;[Solution] C Double Free or Corruption — Freeing Already-Freed Memory Fix&lt;/h1&gt;
&lt;p&gt;A &lt;strong&gt;&amp;ldquo;double free or corruption&amp;rdquo;&lt;/strong&gt; error occurs when your program attempts to &lt;code&gt;free()&lt;/code&gt; a pointer that has already been freed, or when it frees a pointer that was never allocated on the heap. This corrupts the heap metadata used by the memory allocator, which can cause crashes, data corruption, or exploitable security vulnerabilities. The error message typically reads &lt;code&gt;double free or corruption (fasttop)&lt;/code&gt; or &lt;code&gt;double free or corruption (!prev)&lt;/code&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;</description></item><item><title>[Solution] C Invalid free: not a valid pointer</title><link>https://errorcode.excellentwiki.com/languages/c/invalid-free/</link><pubDate>Mon, 01 Jan 0001 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate><guid>https://errorcode.excellentwiki.com/languages/c/invalid-free/</guid><description>&lt;h1 id="invalid-free-not-a-valid-pointer"&gt;Invalid free: not a valid pointer&lt;/h1&gt;
&lt;p&gt;An invalid free occurs when you call &lt;code&gt;free()&lt;/code&gt; on a pointer that was not returned by &lt;code&gt;malloc()&lt;/code&gt;, &lt;code&gt;calloc()&lt;/code&gt;, or &lt;code&gt;realloc()&lt;/code&gt;. This corrupts the heap and causes undefined behavior.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h2 id="common-causes"&gt;Common Causes&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;div class="highlight"&gt;&lt;pre tabindex="0" style="color:#f8f8f2;background-color:#272822;-moz-tab-size:4;-o-tab-size:4;tab-size:4;-webkit-text-size-adjust:none;"&gt;&lt;code class="language-c" data-lang="c"&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#75715e"&gt;// Cause 1: Freeing stack memory
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;int&lt;/span&gt; x &lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;=&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#ae81ff"&gt;5&lt;/span&gt;;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#a6e22e"&gt;free&lt;/span&gt;(&lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;&amp;amp;&lt;/span&gt;x); &lt;span style="color:#75715e"&gt;// invalid — x is on stack
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#75715e"&gt;// Cause 2: Freeing string literal
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;char&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;*&lt;/span&gt;str &lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;=&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#e6db74"&gt;&amp;#34;hello&amp;#34;&lt;/span&gt;;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#a6e22e"&gt;free&lt;/span&gt;(str); &lt;span style="color:#75715e"&gt;// invalid — string literal
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#75715e"&gt;// Cause 3: Freeing already-freed pointer
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;int&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;*&lt;/span&gt;p &lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;=&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#a6e22e"&gt;malloc&lt;/span&gt;(&lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;sizeof&lt;/span&gt;(&lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;int&lt;/span&gt;));
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#a6e22e"&gt;free&lt;/span&gt;(p);
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#a6e22e"&gt;free&lt;/span&gt;(p); &lt;span style="color:#75715e"&gt;// invalid — double free
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#75715e"&gt;// Cause 4: Freeing non-heap pointer
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;int&lt;/span&gt; arr[&lt;span style="color:#ae81ff"&gt;10&lt;/span&gt;];
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#a6e22e"&gt;free&lt;/span&gt;(arr); &lt;span style="color:#75715e"&gt;// invalid — array on stack
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;h2 id="how-to-fix"&gt;How to Fix&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;h3 id="fix-1-only-free-heap-allocated-memory"&gt;Fix 1: Only free heap-allocated memory&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;div class="highlight"&gt;&lt;pre tabindex="0" style="color:#f8f8f2;background-color:#272822;-moz-tab-size:4;-o-tab-size:4;tab-size:4;-webkit-text-size-adjust:none;"&gt;&lt;code class="language-c" data-lang="c"&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;int&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;*&lt;/span&gt;p &lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;=&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#a6e22e"&gt;malloc&lt;/span&gt;(&lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;sizeof&lt;/span&gt;(&lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;int&lt;/span&gt;));
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#a6e22e"&gt;free&lt;/span&gt;(p); &lt;span style="color:#75715e"&gt;// valid
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;h3 id="fix-2-dont-free-string-literals"&gt;Fix 2: Don&amp;rsquo;t free string literals&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;div class="highlight"&gt;&lt;pre tabindex="0" style="color:#f8f8f2;background-color:#272822;-moz-tab-size:4;-o-tab-size:4;tab-size:4;-webkit-text-size-adjust:none;"&gt;&lt;code class="language-c" data-lang="c"&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;char&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;*&lt;/span&gt;str &lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;=&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#a6e22e"&gt;strdup&lt;/span&gt;(&lt;span style="color:#e6db74"&gt;&amp;#34;hello&amp;#34;&lt;/span&gt;);
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#a6e22e"&gt;free&lt;/span&gt;(str); &lt;span style="color:#75715e"&gt;// valid — strdup allocates
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;h3 id="fix-3-set-to-null-after-free"&gt;Fix 3: Set to NULL after free&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;div class="highlight"&gt;&lt;pre tabindex="0" style="color:#f8f8f2;background-color:#272822;-moz-tab-size:4;-o-tab-size:4;tab-size:4;-webkit-text-size-adjust:none;"&gt;&lt;code class="language-c" data-lang="c"&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;int&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;*&lt;/span&gt;p &lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;=&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#a6e22e"&gt;malloc&lt;/span&gt;(&lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;sizeof&lt;/span&gt;(&lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;int&lt;/span&gt;));
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#a6e22e"&gt;free&lt;/span&gt;(p);
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;p &lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;=&lt;/span&gt; NULL; &lt;span style="color:#75715e"&gt;// free(NULL) is safe
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;h2 id="examples"&gt;Examples&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;div class="highlight"&gt;&lt;pre tabindex="0" style="color:#f8f8f2;background-color:#272822;-moz-tab-size:4;-o-tab-size:4;tab-size:4;-webkit-text-size-adjust:none;"&gt;&lt;code class="language-c" data-lang="c"&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#75715e"&gt;#include&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#75715e"&gt;&amp;lt;stdio.h&amp;gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#75715e"&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#75715e"&gt;#include&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#75715e"&gt;&amp;lt;stdlib.h&amp;gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#75715e"&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#75715e"&gt;#include&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#75715e"&gt;&amp;lt;string.h&amp;gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#75715e"&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;int&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#a6e22e"&gt;main&lt;/span&gt;(&lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;void&lt;/span&gt;) {
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#75715e"&gt;// Valid: heap-allocated
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;char&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;*&lt;/span&gt;heap_str &lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;=&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#a6e22e"&gt;strdup&lt;/span&gt;(&lt;span style="color:#e6db74"&gt;&amp;#34;hello&amp;#34;&lt;/span&gt;);
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#a6e22e"&gt;free&lt;/span&gt;(heap_str);
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt; 
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#75715e"&gt;// Invalid: stack memory
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#75715e"&gt;// char stack_str[10] = &amp;#34;hello&amp;#34;;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#75715e"&gt;// free(stack_str); // DON&amp;#39;T DO THIS
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt; 
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#75715e"&gt;// Invalid: string literal
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#75715e"&gt;// char *lit = &amp;#34;hello&amp;#34;;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#75715e"&gt;// free(lit); // DON&amp;#39;T DO THIS
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt; 
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;return&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#ae81ff"&gt;0&lt;/span&gt;;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;}
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;h2 id="related-errors"&gt;Related Errors&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;a href="https://errorcode.excellentwiki.com/languages/c/double-free-heap/"&gt;Double free&lt;/a&gt; — freeing twice.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;a href="https://errorcode.excellentwiki.com/languages/c/use-after-free-heap/"&gt;Use after free&lt;/a&gt; — accessing freed memory.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;a href="https://errorcode.excellentwiki.com/languages/c/heap-corruption/"&gt;Heap corruption&lt;/a&gt; — heap damage.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;</description></item><item><title>[Solution] C Memory Leak — Valgrind Lost Bytes / Still Reachable Fix</title><link>https://errorcode.excellentwiki.com/languages/c/memory-leak/</link><pubDate>Mon, 01 Jan 0001 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate><guid>https://errorcode.excellentwiki.com/languages/c/memory-leak/</guid><description>&lt;h1 id="solution-c-memory-leak--valgrind-lost-bytes--still-reachable-fix"&gt;[Solution] C Memory Leak — Valgrind Lost Bytes / Still Reachable Fix&lt;/h1&gt;
&lt;p&gt;A &lt;strong&gt;memory leak&lt;/strong&gt; occurs when your program allocates heap memory (via &lt;code&gt;malloc&lt;/code&gt;, &lt;code&gt;calloc&lt;/code&gt;, or &lt;code&gt;realloc&lt;/code&gt;) but fails to &lt;code&gt;free()&lt;/code&gt; it before the pointer is lost. Valgrind reports this as &lt;code&gt;&amp;quot;definitely lost: N bytes in M blocks&amp;quot;&lt;/code&gt; or &lt;code&gt;&amp;quot;still reachable: N bytes&amp;quot;&lt;/code&gt;. While small leaks may be harmless in short-lived programs, large or repeated leaks exhaust memory and cause performance degradation or crashes.&lt;/p&gt;</description></item></channel></rss>